    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# mapOfferingToSubscription transforms service offering state into subscription initialization\n\nLocated at `editors/subscription-instance-editor/components/mapOfferingToSubscription.ts`, this function bridges the ServiceOffering and SubscriptionInstance models.\n\n## What It Does\n\nTakes a ServiceOffering's state plus user selections and produces an `InitializeSubscriptionInput` for the SubscriptionInstance model:\n\n```typescript\ninterface MapOfferingOptions {\n  // ServiceOffering state + user selections \u2192 SubscriptionInstance init\n}\nfunction mapOfferingToSubscription(options: MapOfferingOptions): InitializeSubscriptionInput\n```\n\n## Internal Helpers\n\n- `mapServiceGroups()` \u2014 Maps offering groups to subscription groups with tier pricing\n- `mapGroupServices()` \u2014 Maps services within a group based on tier service levels\n- `mapStandaloneServices()` \u2014 Maps services not assigned to any group\n- `mapUsageLimits()` \u2014 Converts usage limits to metrics with free/paid thresholds\n\n## Used By\n\n- `ImportServiceConfigButton.tsx` in the subscription-instance editor \u2014 the \"import from offering\" action\n\nSince [[five models form a hierarchy from facet through template to offering to subscription to instance]], this function is the primary bridge between the offering definition phase and the subscription activation phase.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[helper functions]]\n- [[object relations]]\n- [[model-editor wiring]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z"
    }
  },
